history.content:
You will lose your spot on the waitlist.

Dropping off a waitlist and re-adding yourself will never help your enrollment chances unless there are more spaces available in the class than there are people on the existing waitlist.

More importantly, if telebears has you select a secondary section (e.g., discussion or lab) is that you can change the secondary section you are waitlisted for in telebears without dropping off the lecture waitlist.  If you are currently waitlisted for a full discussion with a long waitlist, moving to a discussion section that has space and/or a much shorter waitlist will increase your chances for enrollment.
If I'm on a manual waitlist but the online schedule shows 1 spot in the class should i drop the course and take the one spot or will i only lose my spot on the waitlist?
